name: Medical Examiner Seeks Public’s Help Identifying Jane Doe
description: The San Diego County Medical Examiner’s Office is seeking the public’s help in identifying a woman who was found unresponsive on Jan. 10, 2025, at approximately 11 p.m. in the parking lot of Palomar Street MTS Station in Chula Vista.

affiliation.name: County of San Diego Communications Office

articleContent:
Reading Time:  < 1 minuteThe San Diego County Medical Examiner’s Office is seeking the public’s help in identifying a woman who was found unresponsive on Jan. 10, 2025, at approximately 11 p.m. in the parking lot of Palomar Street MTS Station in Chula Vista.
The woman was transported to Scripps Mercy Hospital Chula Vista where her death was pronounced a short time later, the Medical Examiner’s Office said.
Despite extensive efforts, investigators have not been able to identify the woman and are asking for the public’s help in case they may recognize her unique tattoos or her description.
The Medical Examiner describes her as Hispanic or bi-racial, between the ages of 18 and 25 years old, approximately 5 feet 1 inches tall, and 166 pounds.
She had wavy black hair and brown eyes. She had several unique tattoos including a rose on the outer corner of the left eye, “Samantha” on the right rib cage, the outline of a heart on the right chest, and a money bag on the right ring finger.
Anyone who believes they may know the woman’s identity is asked to contact the Medical Examiner’s Investigations Unit at (858) 694-2905. The case number is 2025-00128.
